Description: The Restaurant List Company, started by Jeff Gould and Marc Fortune — long-time business acquaintances and successful entrepreneurs
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: The Restaurant List Company, started by Jeff Gould and Marc Fortune — long-time business acquaintances and successful entrepreneurs — was created to provide hotels with a list of restaurants in close proximity.  "The whole concept is so simple, and provides a valuable service to the restaurants, the hotels and the hotel's guests," said Jeff Gould, co-founder of The Restaurant List Company.   Restaurants that sign on with The Restaurant List Company are able to reach customers who are making an immediate decision about where to eat.  The List gives these hotel guests specific restaurant choices near the hotel and a map showing how to get there.   "With The List, a hotel can provide its guests with a choice of over 30 restaurants, in all dining categories and prices," said Marc Fortune, co-founder of The Restaurant List Company.  "And they have a professionally printed document with a map on the back to show where each restaurant is in proximity to the hotel, as well as local attractions."  Investors have also seen the wisdom of the simple business put together by Fortune and Gould as the Restaurant List Company has raised $1.6 million in startup capital.  The investment was led by Solidus Company with participation from Nashville Capital Network angels, the NCN Angel Fund, and a number of individual Nashville and Atlanta investors.   Speaking for Solidus, Managing Partner Townes Duncan said, "The Restaurant List Company is the perfect type of investment for Solidus Partners.  It is simple to understand, it is built for the long-term, and the principals have proven in past ventures that they know how to build value.  We are excited about the company's growth potential over the next few years."   Sid Chambless, executive director of Nashville Capital Network, commented on the investment in The Restaurant List Company: "Nashville Capital Network has a long standing relationship with the management team of The Restaurant List Company.  Because of their track record and the promise of this opportunity, NCN's fund joined several of our angel group members in helping capitalize the company."   Gould and Fortune are currently launching their product in the Nashville area and are planning to be in at least five Southeast markets by the end of 2009. They are planning a national launch within the first two years of operation.
Industry Groups: Financial Services, Food and Beverage, Lending and Investments

Description: DiabetesManager.com is an Internet-based medical service providing the decision support you need to optimally control your diabetes.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: DiabetesManager.com was founded for the purpose of bringing better care to people with diabetes. The Diabetes Control and Complications Trial (DCCT), a 10-year study examining the effects of blood glucose control on the development of complications of diabetes published in 1993, clearly demonstrated a dramatic reduction in the risk and/or severity of diabetes-related complications in patients with Type 1 diabetes undergoing intensive diabetes management.  The UKPDS, a British study, revealed the same results in people with Type 2 diabetes.  Unfortunately, the cost and resources required to provide the intensive management truly necessary to deliver on the promise of the DCCT and UKPDS have drastically limited most people's opportunity to access such care. DiabetesManager.com was founded to bring most of the features of intensive diabetes management, including intelligent home care decision-support to diabetics everywhere at a reasonable cost.

Description: Social Bookmarking with Twitter
Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Krumlr is social bookmarking site that allows users to bookmark URLs while they tweet about them to Twitter. Krumlr users can drag a link to their browser that will automatically copy the URL of the open page, then shorten it and append to their comment as a tweet to Twitter.  In the same step Krumlr will also categorize, tag and save the "krum" to their Krumlr profile. Krumlr's has a follow-me, follow-you  interface (similar to Twitter's) making it easy to discover what pages other Krumstrs are bookmarking  and tweeting about (TweetMarking). To see what another Krumstr is doing, simply click on their profile. To track multiple users, follow them and their "krums" will appear on your Trail Krum page. Krumlr has thousand of tagged links that can be searched, picked up, or retweeted with a simple click. For feedback, Krumlr tracks your tweets. This includes number of clicks, where (by country IP), and time since tweet. Krumlr ranks users by activity and lists pages chronologically or by popularity. Krumlr uses Twitter OAuth so Krumstrs can share their URLs but not their passwords.
